theorem Topology.denseInterior_implies_P3 {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Dense (interior (A : Set X)) → Topology.P3 (X:=X) A := by
  intro hDense
  dsimp [Topology.P3]
  intro x hxA
  -- `interior A ⊆ A`, hence `closure (interior A) ⊆ closure A`
  have h_subset : closure (interior (A : Set X)) ⊆ closure A :=
    closure_mono (interior_subset : interior (A : Set X) ⊆ A)
  -- Since `interior A` is dense, its closure is the whole space
  have h_cl_inner : closure (interior (A : Set X)) = (Set.univ : Set X) :=
    hDense.closure_eq
  -- Therefore `closure A` is also the whole space
  have h_clA : closure (A : Set X) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    have h_univ_subset : (Set.univ : Set X) ⊆ closure A := by
      simpa [h_cl_inner] using h_subset
    exact Set.Subset.antisymm (Set.Subset_univ _) h_univ_subset
  -- Hence the interior of `closure A` is the whole space
  have h_int : interior (closure (A : Set X)) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    simpa [h_clA, interior_univ]
  -- The desired inclusion is now immediate
  simpa [h_int] using (by
    simp : (x : X) ∈ (Set.univ : Set X))

theorem Set.Subset_univ {α : Type*} {s : Set α} : s ⊆ (Set.univ : Set α) := by
  intro x hx
  simp
